Package: mysterymaps
Title: Geographic Mapping Tools for Mystery-Caller Healthcare Studies
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Tyler", "Muffly", email = "tyler.muffly@dhha.org", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2044-1693"))
Description: Companion mapping package for the 'mysterycall' mystery-caller study
    framework. Provides geographic visualisation tools including isochrone (drive-time)
    polygon generation via the HERE Routing API, choropleth maps of acceptance rates by
    US state, Hospital Referral Region (HRR) spatial overlays, ACOG district boundaries,
    leaflet base maps, physician dot maps, and census block-group overlap calculations.
    Intended for use alongside 'mysterycall' when geographic access analyses are needed.
